  "body": "Refactor certain parts of the test case suite into more general [fuzzer-based](https://www.owasp.org/index.php/Fuzzing) test cases (using [Hypothesis](https://hypothesis.works/) or other lib)\r\n\r\nExamples of valuable uses:\r\n- \"Bad code\"/\"Good code\" compile checks\r\n  - no assertions about the code, only that it compiles\r\n  - example [here](https://github.com/ethereum/vyper/blob/1cd54f7530544d661b76d12f76de5a643254b99e/tests/parser/syntax/test_custom_units.py#L14)\r\n- Validate type clamps at ABI level\r\n  - bypasses eth-abi/web3py\r\n  - maybe symbolic analysis is better?\r\n\r\nIt's important to note that fuzzing must be applied intelligently to scenarios where a strategy can be constructed simply without re-implementing the functionality under test. For example, `hypothesis` has a [plugin](https://hypothesis.readthedocs.io/en/latest/extras.html#hypothesis-lark) for the `lark` parser that can generate different sequences of tokens, which may be useful.",
